<br>
I generally try to give pets back, IF it's not too much of a pain. I think we all do.<br>
<br>
But, there are problems with positioning. Sometimes the slow pulls it off us- And if that bloody shammy or enchanter is far away and up a freaking wall... (had this happen last night) the mob will move far, and it's hard to get it back into a good position. Nukes, etc, can also do this.<br>
<br>
Also, as was mentioned, mobs move even if you don't. Mobs move YOU even if you don't move. I joke about melee-range summoning, but it sucks, really. All of a sudden you get summoned, and most of the time you have to move again to get back into melee range- You end up behind the mob. Hits push the mob- It happens. Or you get knocked back a bit and the mob takes a step forward. Or the monks/etc push it in a ring around you.<br>
<br>
What am I saying? Usually, it's easy to position mobs if you give it half a effort. But several things can happen to lose the good position, and a lot of it, not much the warrior can do but regain aggro and deal with it being messed up.<br>
<br>
One of those things could be it's been several hours grinding xp and you just got a mage, and aren't thinking about it. :-)<br>
<br>
We just need to work together. Not be the warrior who doesn't pay attention, not be the mage who attacks before it's in camp, and not be the bloody shammy who is up the freaking hill and slowling early. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://photo5.matchnet.com/alpha/2003/01/24/15703897.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17853" target="top">My Stuffages</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tashant>Tashant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/5/03 9:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1949.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: How hard is it (really) to position mobs?</span><hr size=1> I have a 65 warrior, but used to play a necro as my main, he's 59. When I played my necro, I usually figured out where the tank liked to pull the mob to, and which way he likes to face (maybe there's a serene pond out there or something <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), and then I tell my pet to guard behind where the war pulls, so when I send him to attack he's already facing the right way. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:times new roman;font-size:medium;">The below statement is true <br>
